   BUSH: I'm going to put conservative people in the cabinet. It's
none of my business what somebody _ now, when somebody makes it my
business, like on gay marriage, I'm going to stand up and say I
don't support gay marriage. I support marriage between men and
women.
</P>
<P>
   KING: So therefore if a state were voting on gay marriage, you
would suggest to that state not to approve it.
