   THE LAYOUT'S DONE FOR YOU: Stories marked as a CoxNet layout are
available for purchase in paginated form:
http://nytsyn.com/syndicate/pageex.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   BUYER'S-EDGE _ Mixing and matching is still the hottest trend in
china buying. Brides to be are doing it _ and matrons who chose
their patterns decades ago are selecting complementary patterns to
update their tables without discarding the old. Here's how to do
it. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-GUIDE _ A weekly feature telling how to locate
hard-to-fnd items. This week: White Wizard Cleaner, Cartier's So
Pretty fragranc e, Tofutti frozen dessert and a First Alert fire
escape ladder. (MJohnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-DESTINATION _ A weekly feature about fun places to shop
in the Southeast. This week: Rome, Ga. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (EDS: Moving on l (Lifestyle) and a
(General News) categories.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-POTROAST _ In the dead of winter, pot roast is the ultimate
comfort food. We give the technique for how to cook it to
perfection, and offer recipes both for Mom's version and some with
ethnic twists. plus recipes for getting more mileage out of the
leftovers: a pasta sauce, a hero sandwich. (Kessler, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH COLOR PHOTO.
</P>
