   FOOD-SKUBE-BEERCOLUMN _ Michael Skube's beer column is not
available this week. (Skube, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CYBERSPICE _ A weekly column looking at the plethora of
recipes on the Internet. (Parham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DIETITIAN _ Dietitian column. This week: Plant grains versus
refined flour, lowering your cholesterol by altering your diet and
fruit snacks. (Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   COMFORTFOOD-BOOKS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ It takes only a
slight dip in the temperature to send us searching for comfort
foods: hot casseroles, pot pies and roasts with vegetables. Three
new cookbooks address this style of cooking and can help you
produce something warm and steamy from the oven. (Norris, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet FOOD page for the current week.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0215 -- Cubed or shredded, fried potato variations
made from scratch provide the perfect payoff. (Heller, Dayton Daily
News) Art includes 3-column color photo of has browns.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FRESH OR FROZEN BOX -- Tips on making hash browns from fresh or
frozen potatoes. (Heller, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   RECIPES _ Lyonaise Potatoes and Classic Hash Browns.
