<P>
   BROWN-PROBE (San Francisco)_ Expanding its probe at San
Francisco City Hall, a U.S. grand jury is scrutinizing financial
deals involving Mayor Willie Brown's office and his friend Charlie
Walker, federal subpoenas show. In four subpoenas issued from June
through January, the grand jury told the mayor's staff to turn over
records involving businesses through which Walker, a political
supporter and former law client of Brown, has sought city funds
since Brown became mayor in 1996. By LANCE WILLIAMS and CHUCK
FINNIE.
</P>
<P>
   COLORED-TIRES (San Francisco) _ Though a tire company executive
paid a visit to the San Francisco Board of Supervisors to try to
dispel opposition to his company's new colored tires, members of a
supervisors committee decided to stick to a plan to ban the sale of
the controversial tires in San Francisco. By TYCHE HENDRICKS.
</P>
