in the Amadou Diallo trial and I still don't know what to make of
it. Were those cops jumpy when they approached Diallo, a young West
African immigrant living in the Bronx? Given that 30 New York City
police officers have been gunned down since 1990, the cops had
ample reason to be jumpy _ especially at night in a high-crime
neighborhood and with a guy who wasn't showing them his hands as
they say they ordered him to do. By DAN LYNCH.
