</P>
<P>
   As Iran's most popular female politician, Jamileh Kadivar is
routinely forced to maneuver through the minefield of being a
feminist and an Islamic activist, of which she is both. Now, on the
eve of her country's election this Friday, Feb. 18, Mrs. Kadivar
finds herself at the center of one of Iran's leading political
families. &QL;
