   &UR; JEWS CLAIM HAIDER STOLE THEIR `VALLEY OF THE BEARS' &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Deep in the mountains of Austria's rural southern Carinthia
region, the Baerental forest extends over 1,600 hectares (4,000
acres). It is prime timber and hunting land that has helped build
the fortune of its owner, the governor of Carinthia and the leader
of the far-right Austrian Freedom Party, Joerg Haider. But the
Jewish family that was forced to sell the ``Valley of the Bears''
on the eve of WWII, in a murky transaction involving Haider's
relatives and blocked bank accounts, says the sale was illegal and
immoral. Now, the family wants justice. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Peter S. Green, International Herald Tribune &QL;
