<P>
   (Commentary) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Anyone who seeks the roots of Joerg Haider's ideas in the Nazi
era is wrong. The roots go much deeper and are, in a way, much more
sinister. Anyone who wants to understand the origins and texture of
the Haider phenomenon should go back to 1895-1897. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Shlomo Avineri, International Herald Tribune &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Moved Feb. 15) &QL;
</P>
