<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    GRAPEVINE
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Lots of announcements from WWF promotions. The next
music CD is expected to be released March 21 and should be called
``Aggression.'' Meanwhile, three new videos are scheduled to hit
shelves April 25. They are ``The Rock: The People's Champ,'' ``Mick
Foley: Wild Man Un-Masked'' and ``Eve of Destruction.''
</P>
<P>
   Ratings for ECW on TNN jumped up 0.1 point this week to 1.1.
They continue to be TNN's top-rated show.
</P>
<P>
   It was originally going to be a Canadian super-match between the
country's top two stars, Bret Hart and Chris Benoit, for the Feb.
26 house show in Winnipeg, Manitoba. When Benoit left WCW, the card
was switched to Bret Hart vs. Sid. Now the ads are touting Sid vs.
Scott Hall, but that match might be in jeopardy also.
</P>
<P>
   WWF stock may have finally bottomed out. News of the XFL
football league has sent investors running to sell and the stock
plunged to an all-time low of 10 3/4. On Monday of this week it
jumped to 11 5/8 and is expected to climb slightly as the stock is
considered a great value under $13.
</P>
<P>
   On the WWF injury front, Eddy Guerrero had his cast taken off
his arm and he may return to the mat in just a month, ahead of the
orginal diagnosis of three to four months. Matt Hardy injured his
shoulder at a house show in Austin, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   On the rumor killer tour, Shawn Michaels will not become the
third member of the WWF announcing team, although many feel he does
good work as a mouthpiece. Michaels did get some of his wrestlers
(from Shawn Michaels' Texas Wrestling Alliance) developmental
contracts with the WWF. Lance Cade, American Dragon, Spanky and
Shooter Schultz also signed deals.
</P>
<P>
   While it appears as though they have joined DX, most don't
expect the Radicals affiliation to last long. Expect them to become
fan favorites soon after ``Wrestlemania'' in April. Vince McMahon
may return also, but only if the television ratings start to sag;
the Hemsley-McMahon era has really taken off in the ratings.
</P>
<P>
   Looking for a new web site? Try mickfoley.com, which just
launched.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of Websites, wwf.com set a record with 184 million page
hits in January.
</P>
<P>
   Jim Ross reports that with over 600,000 buys, the ``2000 Royal
Rumble'' ranks behind only last year's event as the most watched
Royal Rumble ever.
</P>
<P>
   Raven may be developing his own flock in ECW with Mikey
Whipwreck, Francine and possibly Tommy Dreamer.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
