<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GAME-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    ECW enters the hot video-game market
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   It's taken awhile, but Extreme Championship Wrestling is
breaking into the final frontier of sports entertainment
money-making _ video games.
</P>
<P>
   For the past few years, some of the most popular video games
have been wrestling oriented. The World Wrestling Federation and
World Championship Wrestling have found a cash cow in the world of
video games.
</P>
<P>
   This week, ECW joins the market with its first video game _
``ECW Hardcore Revolution'' _ from Acclaim Entertainment Inc. The
game will be available for the Sony Playstation and Color Game Boy
and scheduled for release on Sega Dreamcast in early March.
</P>
<P>
   ``While others have tried to imitate, ECW is the innovator of
hardcore wrestling,'' said Michael Jerchower, the director of
licensing for Acclaim. ``Just as ECW has set the standard in
extreme wrestling, `ECW Hardcore Revolution' will set the strandard
for wrestling video games.''
</P>
<P>
   To that end, the game has incorporated some of the most violent
moves of some of the most extreme wrestlers in ECW. One of the new
looks is that players can wrestle in the infamous barbed-wire
match, in which the ropes are replaced with barbed-wire. Add to
this the use of weapons, such as cheese graters, kendo-sticks,
bats, shovels and ladders, and the results are bloody wrestlers for
a mature game player.
</P>
<P>
   Acclaim's press releases say theirs is the first mature-rated
wrestling video game, intended for audiences 17 and older. In
addition to the blood-letting, the wrestlers use adult language.
There is no nudity.
</P>
<P>
   The partnership of ECW and Acclaim is unique. When Acclaim got
``exclusive, long-term interactive software'' license rights from
ECW, they also got a minority equity interest in ECW.
</P>
<P>
   ``Acclaim is the most experienced, creative and successful
interactive entertainment partner when it comes to producing
wrestling titles,'' ECW executive producer Paul Heyman said. ``If
you are a fan of wrestling, this will be a must-buy video-game
title.''
</P>
<P>
   As expected, the ECW game has been compared with the products of
the big two _ WWF's ``Warzone,'' ``Attitude,'' ``Smackdown'' and
``Wrestlemaina 2000''; and WCW's ``Mayhem'' and ``WCW/NWO
Revenge.'' But it has its differences and will have a definite
appeal from the millions of people who watch ECW on television.
</P>
<P>
   While ECW joined in the war in the video game market late, it is
unlikely to win the war soon. But it has its sights set on WCW for
second place.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
