<SLUG> BC-MCCAIN-KGB-SPY?-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`MANCHURIAN CANDIDATE' MCCAIN ACCUSED OF BEING A KGB SPY  
 
</HEADLINE>
   (This 425-word ``separate-buy'' article is from THE INDEPENDENT
newspaper in London.)  
  
 (EDITORS: We regret that this material is NOT available to clients
in Canada EXCEPT to The Hamilton (Ontario) Spectator.)  
  
 (To publish this article, it must be purchased from the New York
Times Syndicate's sales representative DEBRA WEYDERT at
732-390-4480, or fax her at 732-390-4697. Her e-mail address is
weyded(at)nytimes.com. If unable to reach Ms. Weydert, please call
800-444-0267, or fax us at 816-822-1444.)  
  
 (PLEASE NOTE: This article has been transmitted into the ``p''
political news, ``a'' domestic/general news and ``k'' commentary
news files.)  
  
 By ANDREW MARSHALL  
 c.2000 The Independent, London  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ John McCain, the Republican challenger for the
party's White House nomination, has been accused of virtually
everything else in an increasingly nasty campaign.
</P>
<P>
   But now he is being labelled a KGB spy, a traitor and perhaps
even a brainwashed zombie controlled by Communists, in a smear that
veers between the comic and the vile.
</P>
<P>
   Right-wing fringe groups hate McCain, a former prisoner of war
in Vietnam. He has not supported their crusade to free the
prisoners they believe remain behind in Southeast Asia after the
Vietnam War, and has backed a resumption of relations with Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
   Though comic, the accusations will harm McCain among some of the
veterans in South Carolina, a crucial element in the state's
primary.
</P>
<P>
   Ted Sampley, a veteran from North Carolina who runs a
newsletter, accuses McCain of betraying his country while a
prisoner, wearing medals that he is not entitled to and even being
a KGB spy.
</P>
<P>
   A former KGB official has said that the Russians ``turned'' a
``high-ranking naval officer'' during interrogation, he says. This
man ``agreed to work with the Soviets upon his repatriation to the
United States and has frequently appeared on U.S. television.''
</P>
<P>
   But he has also made an even more bizarre accusation against
McCain.
</P>
<P>
   ``In the movie `The Manchurian Candidate,' actor Lawrence Harvey
portrayed the character of a former POW and war hero of the Korean
War, whose brainwashing by his communist captors resulted in his
enemies being able to manipulate his actions,'' he says.
</P>
<P>
   ``To trigger him to do their bidding all they had to do was have
him play solitaire with the Queen of Diamonds being the trigger
that made him theirs, body and soul.''
</P>
<P>
   He goes on to ask Senator McCain, rhetorically: ``Have the
Vietnamese flipped you a Queen of Diamonds?''
</P>
<P>
   The ridiculous accusation has been given wide circulation by
conservative activist Paul Weyrich. Weyrich also quotes an
authority that would not normally be compelling.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Cambodian Khmer Rouge has claimed that McCain is a
Vietnamese agent, for whatever that is worth,'' he says.
</P>
<P>
   Weyrich does not definitively say that he believes McCain is
working for SMERSH, but he does hint pretty broadly. ``The charges
are reminiscent of those against Bill Clinton in 1992. It is hard
to know who is telling the truth in all of this,'' he says.
</P>
<P>
   ``It may not always be true that where there is smoke there is
fire, but many times it is true.'' &QL; 
 &UR; ___________________ &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; (To publish this 425-word article from THE INDEPENDENT newspaper in
