<P>
   &UR; HILLARY, HILLARY, WHATEVER HAS HAPPENED TO YOU? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ If past performance is any measure, there is no
doubt that in Senator Hillary Clinton, the people of New York would
have a tough, feisty and intelligent woman standing up for their
interests. That Hillary, though, must have slipped out of the back
door of her new home in Chappaqua, N.Y. The woman who stood in her
raincoat and sensible shoes by the front gate on moving day was but
a caricature. Surely she was an imposter. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Mary Dejevsky, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
