   &UR; `MANCHURIAN CANDIDATE' MCCAIN ACCUSED OF BEING A KBG SPY &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ John McCain, the Republican challenger for the
party's White House nomination, has been accused of virtually
everything else in an increasingly nasty campaign. But now he is
being labelled a KGB spy, a traitor and perhaps even a brainwashed
zombie controlled by Communists, in a smear that veers between the
comic and the vile. Although absurd, the accusations will harm
McCain among some of the veterans in South Carolina, a crucial
element in the state's primary Saturday. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Andrew Marshall, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
