<P>
   WASHINGTON _ It has been four years in the making, and cost
Microsoft some $8 billion to produce. Now, Windows 2000, the
software giant's latest offering is ready to make its debut this
Thursday, Feb. 17. But will it sell? And more importantly, can
Windows 2000 underpin the company's future as its management hopes?
That question, more than the antitrust case against Microsoft, may
determine the company's future. &QL;
