<HEADLINE>
DELECTABLE RECIPES FROM FAR FLUNG CATERERS
</HEADLINE>
 
(Accompanies BC-GOURMET-RAFTING) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   LAMB PROVENCAL
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 tablespoons minced fresh garlic
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 tablespoon olive oil
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh rosemary
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 1/2 pounds (2 racks) trimmed rack of lamb
</P>
<P>
   Combine mustard, garlic, olive oil, rosemary, salt and pepper
into a paste. Rub generously into lamb. Let marinate in
refrigerator for 1 hour. Cook to desired temperature over a hot
charcoal fire.
</P>
<P>
   NUTRITIONAL ANALYSIS PER SERVING: 354 calories, 20 grams fat, 1
gram carbohydrate, 40 grams protein, 129 milligrams cholesterol,
469 milligrams sodium, 52 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Francois Maeder
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   SUNNY FETTUCCINE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   _ 8 ounces spinach fettuccine
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup sun-dried tomatoes, soaked in water to rehydrate
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 cup pine nuts
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 clove finely chopped garlic
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 tablespoons olive oil
</P>
<P>
   _ Coarsely ground black pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   _ Salt to taste
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese
</P>
<P>
   Cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile, slice and
saute sun-dried tomatoes with pine nuts and garlic in olive oil
over medium heat, adding pepper and salt. Drain pasta, toss with
sun-dried tomato mixture and Parmesan. Serve immediately.
</P>
<P>
   NUTRITIONAL ANALYSIS PER SERVING: 407 calories, 26 grams fat, 42
grams carbohydrates, 17 grams protein, 49 milligrams cholesterol,
483 milligrams sodium, 48 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Francois Maeder
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   GRILLED CHICKEN SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Makes 10 servings
</P>
<P>
   _ 4 split chicken breasts, skin and ribs removed
</P>
<P>
   _ 3 Granny Smith apples, cored and coarsely chopped
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup chopped celery
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup chopped red bell pepper
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 cup chopped scallions
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/4 cup Dijon mustard
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 teaspoons dill weed
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
</P>
<P>
   The night before preparing the salad, grill the chicken breasts
over a charcoal fire. Chill in the refrigerator overnight.
</P>
<P>
   Shred chicken coarsely. Mix all ingredients together and serve
on a bed of mixed greens, stuffed into avocado halves, atop melon
slices or on multigrain bread.
</P>
<P>
   NUTRITIONAL ANALYSIS PER SERVING: 268 calories, 13 grams fat, 9
grams carbohydrates, 29 grams protein, 84 milligrams cholesterol,
224 milligrams sodium, 43 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Based on Far Flung Adventures' guides' impromptu preparations
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   FRESH BERRY TRIFLE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 10
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 small sponge cake, recipe follows
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 cups half-and-half
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 12 eggs, beaten
</P>
<P>
   _ 4 egg yolks, beaten
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 ounces dark rum, optional
</P>
<P>
   _ 3 cups fresh raspberries, strawberries or blueberries
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup sliced, toasted almonds
</P>
<P>
   SPONGE CAKE:
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon baking powder
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 cup milk
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/4 cup butter
</P>
<P>
   _ 6 egg yolks
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   TO MAKE SPONGE CAKE: Sift together flour and baking powder. Heat
milk and butter until butter melts. Keep this hot but not boiling.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored. Gradually add sugar
to eggs, beating constantly. Add vanilla. Add flour mixture,
stirring just until mixed. Gently stir in the hot milk mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 9-by-9-by-2-inch pan at 350 degrees for
35 minutes. Cool in pan.
</P>
<P>
   When cake is cooled, carefully cut into three layers.
</P>
<P>
   Make custard by combining half-and-half with sugar in a
saucepan, heating over medium heat until nearly boiling. Add eggs
and yolks, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low and stir for one
more minute; remove from heat, pour into bowl and set bowl in a
larger bowl filled with ice to cool the mixture. Add rum and stir
well.
</P>
<P>
   In a trifle or any deep, straight-sided glass bowl, layer sponge
cake, berries, custard mixture and almonds, repeating to make three
layers, ending with almonds on top. Chill and serve.
</P>
<P>
   NUTRITIONAL ANALYSIS PER SERVING: 514 calories, 29 grams fat, 49
grams carbohydrates, 16 grams protein, 499 milligrams cholesterol,
225 milligrams sodium, 51 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ Francois Maeder
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
