<HEADLINE>
HOW TO GOURMET RAFT
</HEADLINE>
 
(Accompanies BC-GOURMET-RAFTING) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Far Flung Adventures typically offers four spring and four fall
gourmet trips. This year's spring schedule is March 3-5, March
30-April 2, April 14-16 and April 28-30. Cost is $650 per person
and includes all meals, wine, water, tents, waterproof gear bags
and river guides. You bring sleeping bags and pads, or rent them
from the outfitter.
</P>
<P>
   Rafting patrons must be in Terlingua _ about a 10-hour drive
from Dallas/Fort Worth, sans stops _ at Far Flung's offices at 9
a.m. Friday. Overnight lodging in Terlingua-Study Butte includes
the very basic Big Bend Motor Inn, about $70 per night. Some guests
prefer the more atmospheric and expensive Gage Hotel in Marathon,
about an hour north of Big Bend National Park. Far Flung has a list
of lodgings.
</P>
<P>
   The rafting trip usually ends about 3 p.m. on Sunday. Far Flung
will provide a good gear list, which includes things like
sunscreen, rain gear, insect repellent and flashlight.
</P>
<P>
   Contact Far Flung Adventures at (915) 371-2489 or go online at
www.farflung.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
