r d BC-PRESIDENTSDAY-TREATS-     02-16 0682
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PRESIDENTSDAY-TREATS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHERRY TREATS: DELICIOUS NODS TO WASHINGTON'S BIRTHDAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News News Service clients) 
By JUNE NAYLOR RODRIGUEZ 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The moment that all hints of Valentine's Day vanish, Presidents
Day is upon us. Meaning, the kids will be getting an extra dose of
George Washington and Abraham Lincoln stories in history class.
</P>
<P>
   To celebrate this holiday in culinary terms means to see what
kinds of delightful noshes can be made with cherries. (It WAS a
young George Washington who couldn't lie about chopping down that
cherry tree, wasn't it?)
</P>
<P>
   Here are some charming cherry recipes for the whole family.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   DRIED-CHERRY MUFFINS
</P>
<P>
   Makes 18 muffins
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup dried, pitted cherries
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup buttermilk
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 3/4 cups unbleached all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 teaspoons baking powder
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon baking soda
</P>
<P>
   _ Pinch of salt
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 stick unsalted butter, room temperature
</P>
<P>
   _ 3/4 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 eggs, slightly beaten
</P>
<P>
   Combine cherries and buttermilk in a small bowl; set aside to
soak for 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Generously butter 18 muffin cups or
line with paper liners.
</P>
<P>
   In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking
soda and salt. In another bowl, cream together the butter and
sugar. Add the eggs and mix thoroughly.
</P>
<P>
   Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and spoon the
cherries and buttermilk into it. Then add butter-sugar mixture. Mix
only until thoroughly blended; do not overmix.
</P>
<P>
   Fill cups two-thirds full with the batter, and bake until a
toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 18 to 20 minutes.
Transfer to a rack and cool. _ ``The New Basics Cookbook'' by Julee
Rosso &AMP; Sheila Lukins (Workman, $19.95)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CHERRY CHUTNEY
</P>
<P>
   Makes 2 cups
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 cups dried, pitted cherries
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 1/4 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 3/4 cup white vinegar
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/4 cup chopped celery
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/4 cup minced fresh ginger
</P>
<P>
   _ 6 tablespoons apple juice
</P>
<P>
   _ 3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   _ 1/2 teaspoon diced red-pepper flakes
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients in a microwavable, 2-quart casserole,
stirring well.
</P>
<P>
   Cook, uncovered, at full power for 6 minutes. Stir, making sure
the sugar has dissolved, and return to microwave. Cook an
additional 8 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Allow chutney to cool to room temperature; cover tightly and
refrigerate. This keeps up to 1 week in the refrigerator.
</P>
<P>
   NOTE: This makes a delicious condiment, hot or cold, for baked
chicken, grilled pork chops or smoked ham. Serve with brown and
wild rice and a salad, and that's dinner.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The New Basics Cookbook'' by Julee Rosso &AMP; Sheila Lukins
(Workman, $19.95)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CHERRY FLIP
</P>
<P>
   Makes 2 servings
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup frozen cherries
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup milk or soy milk
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 to 2 drops almond extract
</P>
<P>
   _ Honey to taste
</P>
<P>
   _ Mint sprigs for garnish
</P>
<P>
   Blend frozen cherries, milk and extract in blender until smooth.
Sweeten with a little honey if desired. Pour into glasses and
decorate with mint sprigs.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Vegetarian Times Cookbook,'' (Macmillan, $14.95)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CHERRY PIZZA
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 to 10 servings
</P>
<P>
   Crust
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup flour
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 stick margarine
</P>
<P>
   _ 2 tablespoons sugar
</P>
<P>
   Filling
</P>
<P>
   _ 8 ounces cream cheese
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 cup powdered sugar
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 small carton Cool Whip
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   Topping
</P>
<P>
   _ 1 can cherry pie filling
</P>
<P>
   _ Shredded coconut for sprinkling
</P>
<P>
   _ Sliced green maraschino cherries
</P>
<P>
   _ Chopped red maraschino cherries
</P>
<P>
   Mix together crust ingredients and pat out on ungreased 12-inch
pizza pan. (Dough will be soft.) Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10
minutes. Remove from oven and cool.
</P>
<P>
   Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar with mixer until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla, and spread over cooled crust.
</P>
<P>
   Top with cherry pie filling, sprinkle with coconut and top with
green cherry slices and chopped maraschino cherries. Chill and
serve.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Presbyterian Women's Cookbook,'' Grapevine, Texas
.MDRV/.MDNM/ (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the
World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
