A8786 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-AUDIO-SOUL17-COX     02-16 0318
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AUDIO-SOUL17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Chocolate Soul' expands on sweet series
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ No more digging through the import sections at record
stores, flipping from college station to college station and
catching an occasional Chocolate Soul when you can.
</P>
<P>
   Well, actually, continue to do those things, if you have. But if
you haven't, Will G. has done some of that pleasurable work for
you.
</P>
<P>
   The creator of what started as a theme for Thursday nights at
downtown Atlanta's Yin Yang Cafe and became a sporadic concert
series with always-worthwhile acts has compiled a strong album
under the locally popular ``Chocolate Soul'' banner.
</P>
<P>
   It starts overseas with London acid jazz band D-Influence easing
through the airy and somewhat lightweight ``Life.'' Two tracks
later, we're back home, and Atlanta's Seek lays more solid musical
footing on ``Ever After.'' Then fellow residents Edith's Wish stomp
all over that footing in the achy, stand-out rocker
``Mockingbird.''
</P>
<P>
   Next stop, Japan, where Satashi Tomiie catches another breezy
jazz feel until the wind delightfully changes into drum and bass at
the bridge of ``Heaven.'' Local oft-noted singer/songwriter Jeffery
Butts offers more of a change in time than place on the early '70s
Sly Stone-inspired ``Amazing,'' which is what Atlanta hip-hop act
Mass Influence is, lyrically anyway, on the lithe ``Rhyme
Placement'' that follows.
</P>
<P>
   ``Chocolate Soul's'' final destination is the mind-set of those
who think R&AMP;B is as limited as commercial radio programming and
many major record label offerings. Feel a little silly now?
</P>
<P>
   R&AMP;B
</P>
<P>
   ``Chocolate Soul Music Compilation''
</P>
<P>
   Various artists. Chocolate Soul Music. 13 tracks.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: A
</P>
<P>
   _Sonia Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
