<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Video spotlight
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Spotlight on Andie MacDowell (``The Muse'')
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The End of Violence'' (1997, R). Dealing with a frayed
marriage to action-flick producer Bill Pullman in Wim Wenders' odd
drama.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Michael'' (1996, PG). Encountering sloppy angel John
Travolta.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Multiplicity'' (1996, PG-13). Encountering multiple versions
of hubby Michael Keaton.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Four Weddings and a Funeral'' (1994, R). Meeting Hugh Grant
at all five rituals of the title, and falling in love.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Groundhog Day'' (1992, PG). Living through the day
repeatedly until weatherman Bill Murray gets it right, and getsher.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Green Card'' (1990, PG-13). Falling for French pianist
Gerard Depardieu.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``sex, lies, and videotape'' (1989, R). Falling for her
husband's old friend, James Spader.
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
