<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WANT DIVIDENDS TO RECIRCULATE? USE A DRIP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: There is a DRIP directory put out by some 900 company for
people who want to invest without going through a broker. Where can
I get this? _ B.D., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: There are several groups providing information on companies
that offer dividend reinvestment plans (DRIPs).
</P>
<P>
   One is the Direct Purchase Plan Clearinghouse, which mails a
free prospectus and enrollment information for more than 350
companies. For information, call (800) 774-4117 or visit the Web
site www.dripinvestor.com.
</P>
<P>
   Another is the National Association of Investors, a nonprofit
group offering a low-cost investment plan, ``Better Investing''
magazine and other services to members who pay $39 a year. Write to
Box 220, Royal Oak, MI 48068, or call (877) 275-6242.
</P>
<P>
   DRIP investors automatically have their stock dividend applied
to the purchase of more shares in a company. Once you have acquired
a share in a company that offers this kind of plan, you can
purchase additional shares directly from the company instead of
going through a broker.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find a coffee mug with a picture of Snoopy lying
atop his doghouse? _ D.K.
</P>
<P>
   A: During the '50s and '60s, Anchor Hocking made white Fire-King
coffee mugs with Snoopy sleeping on his doghouse and the words ``I
Think I'm Allergic to Morning.''
</P>
<P>
   The mug and many other Fire-King collectibles turn up often on
eBay, an Internet auction site you can find at www.ebay.com.
</P>
<P>
   You also may be able to find it from Fire-King dealer R.C. Boyd.
To contact Boyd, write to RC Boyd, RR No. 3, Box 107A, Hunlock
Creek PA 18621, or visit the Web site www.rcboyd.com.
</P>
<P>
   An Internet newsletter for Fire-King collectors is available
from Boyd's Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I can't find the Gardena Co. Where can I find a Gardena Water
Computer with a moisture-meter sensor? _ D.M., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: You can buy Water Computers directly from the Gardena Co. by
calling (540) 722-5600, Ext. 148.
</P>
<P>
   The watering controls for electronic sprinklers sell for $65 to
$107, depending on the model you choose.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
