<HEADLINE>
`KUKLA, FRAN AND OLLIE' ARRIVE ON VIDEO
</HEADLINE>
 (for use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Where can we find ``Kukla, Fran and Ollie'' videos? _
A.C.
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ New Kid Home Video is selling five color videos and
planning 34 more. Current titles are ``Be a Clown, Be a Clown; Get
on the Dragon Wagon; Kukla Discovers America; Madame O's Merry
Musical;'' and ``'Tis the Season to Be Ollie.''
</P>
<P>
   Each video sells for $14.95 plus $4.95 shipping and handling. To
order, call (800) 309-2392 or write to Box 10443, Beverly Hills, CA
90213-3443.
</P>
<P>
   The original ``Kukla, Fran and Ollie'' TV series ran from 1947
to 1957 and was followed by specials, guest appearances and live
performances through the early 1980s. The show was improvised by
puppeteer Burr Tillstrom and actress Fran Allison.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ What does the ``WG'' on a Copenhagen tobacco can stand
for? A colleague claims it is short for ``with glass'' because the
product contains ground-up fiberglass to cut the mouth and ensure
fast absorption. _ P.D., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ The insignia is actually ``WC'' and stands for
``Weyman's Copenhagen,'' according to manufacturer U.S. Tobacco.
</P>
<P>
   ``George Weyman was the founder of Copenhagen in 1822,'' said
U.S. Tobacco spokesman John Atwood.
</P>
<P>
   Although the initials snuff out your colleague's theory, Atwood
made it official: ``Copenhagen doesn't contain fiberglass,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Where can I buy the game Shut the Box? _ W.B., Bedford,
Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ The retailer English Darts Plus sells three wooden
boxes with dice and instructions for Shut the Box: a solid oak box
for $19.49 and walnut-finished boxes for $29.99 or $18.99.
</P>
<P>
   To order, call (888) 281-1477, write to English Darts Plus, 5316
S. 27th St., Milwaukee, WI 53221, or visit the Web site
www.englishdartsplus.com.  &QL;
</P>
