   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-HOTSPORT _ It's hard to put a number on what Tiger Woods'
winning streak meant to the sport of golf, but purses, TV ratings
and interest have never been this high during the month of
February. When his daddy said years ago that he would change the
face of the sport, he probably had no idea. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   GOODWILL-GAMES _ LAKE PLACID, N.Y. _ The Goodwill Games are
back, winter-style. The schedule includes some events and athletes
you'll see at the next Winter Olympics and some you won't. Goodwill
organizers have geared their Games toward four days of prime-time
TV programming. Among the gimmicks: Two downhill events, dual
moguls racing, sprint cross-country skiiing, and two X Games-type
snowboard events. For figure skating, there going with the pros
like Katarina Witt and Oksana Baiul. They passed on hockey, because
not enough good players are available this time of year. And all
winners will receive prize money. (Rosen, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
   SOC-INTLNOTES _ International soccer report. (Parker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
