says, spur economic growth, calm ethnic strife, reduce corruption
and even slow the spread of AIDS. Yet, despite all that, Ouattara
is glad that a coup in December forced his country's president out
of office. Why? Because he thinks the coup will help, rather than
hinder, democracy. Ouattara plans to run for president in elections
he hopes the Carter Center will monitor. (Melvin, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
