federal government plans to deport the deacon because of a 1996
immigration law roundly criticized as unduly harsh. Worry about the
deacon's predicament became the flash point for the first
well-organized political effort among the roughly 50,000 Korean
immigrants in Georgia. (Bixler, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40.
WITH PHOTO.
