<P>
   SCHOOL-FOOD (Los Angeles) _ A new statewide survey of high
school fast food shows that pizza, cookies, chips and other junk
food comprise 70 percent of all food sales on a majority of
campuses. And although schools promote nutritional, healthy meals
they must depend on fast food to keep their cafeterias in the
black. By David R. Baker and Dominic Berbeo. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DEMO-CONVENTION (Los Angeles) _ Determined to prevent the
Democratic National Convention from becoming a huge embarrassment
to Los Angeles, and concerned because planning and organization for
the August event are going so poorly, Mayor Richard Riordan
announced a big shake-up on Wednesday as he put his chief
spokeswoman, Deputy Mayor Noelia Rodriguez, in charge of the local
planning. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
