   IRELAND-PEACE (London) _ British and Irish prime ministers bring
the main parties in Northern Ireland together in an exercise that
only shows how far apart they remain on the vexing question of
disarming the IRA and restoring the power-sharing government. By
Kevin Cullen. 600 words.
</P>
