   CAMPAIGN-GOP (Hilton Head, S.C.) _ Admitting his campaign shed
more than $50 million of its vaunted war chest before Jan. 31,
George W. Bush struggles to defend his rapid spending rate. By
Curtis Wilkie and Anne E. Kornblut. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-GORE (Macon Ga.) _ Blurring the lines between his
presidential campaign and his vice presidential duties, Al Gore
barnstorms the south then surveys damage from the deadliest
tornadoes to hit Georgia in 50 years. By Ann Scales. 850 words.
</P>
