<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-DONNAN-RAMSEY-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Ramsey confronts Donnan in office
 &HT;    By Chip Towers
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATHENS _ Any chance of Kevin Ramsey remaining at Georgia as an
assistant football coach probably ended after a heated
confrontation with coach Jim Donnan on Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   Ramsey, demoted as defensive coordinator early Monday morning,
returned to Butts-Mehre Heritage Hall around noon that day and
argued with Donnan in the head coach's office.
</P>
<P>
   Ramsey would not confirm what happened in the meeting. Donnan
would say only, ``We've got a legal situation and I'm told I can't
comment on anything.''
</P>
<P>
   But Claude Felton, associate athletics director for external
affairs, confirmed that a second meeting took place and that it was
``heated.''
</P>
<P>
   Athletics department officials were extremely guarded Wednesday
in their comments on the situation. ``Anything that took place in
that meeting or any other meetings are personnel matters, and we
can't comment on them,'' Felton said.
</P>
<P>
   Settlement negotiations are under way between Ramsey and the
Georgia Athletic Association. Ramsey, who initially was offered the
opportunity to remain as secondary coach, has 4 1/2 months
remaining on a one-year contract at $130,000.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're talking to Coach Ramsey, trying to figure out what's
going to happen in terms of his career,'' said Athens attorney Ed
Tolley, who represents the athletic association. ``We hope to have
this resolved, really, in the next 48 hours. That's what we're
really working on, trying to keep everybody happy.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
