seeking the first funding increase for his agency in seven years,
appears before a congressional panel to defend the space agency's
reliance on Russia to help it complete the International Space
Station. Panel members criticize NASA for working with the Russian
government instead of private Russian companies, but Goldin says at
least one of those companies had gouged NASA on prices for
hardware. By PATTY REINERT.
