Hand, a metalworker and ex-sculptor with a studio on Leonard Street
in TriBeCa, is the cold-rolled-steel set's current ``It'' Boy.
``It's all the hand finishing,'' he says. Steel is ``pickled,''
Hand explains, with an acid application to remove the ``blue
scale'' it arrives with, then chemically sprayed and scrubbed by
hand, as if it were being waxed, to achieve the required color and
patina. (Philip Greenberg/The New York Times)
