at Adelphi University on Wednesday. Archaeologists think they have
found remains of 200 to 250 Athenian citizen-soldiers. Their ashes
and bones were excavated three years ago at a construction site in
Athens, but now they have been delivered to the university for the
first detailed scientific analysis. (Maxine Hicks/The New York
