Delegate James H. Dillard II at the Virginia State Legislature in
Richmond. Dillard's proposals to ban guns and hunting on Virginia's
school grounds were snuffed in committee while the House passed a
lawsuit ban (promoted by the National Rifle Association against
cities suing gun manufacturers for liability in deadly sprees by
citizens) and sent it to the Senate. ``School districts were
begging for passage of my bills, but it didn't matter,'' Dillard
ruefully observes. (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
