Replacing a hammer handle is not a difficult task, but first you
must remove the old handle. Begin by sawing off the damaged handle
just below the base of the hammerhead. Use a punch to drive the
remaining portion out of the ``eye.'' If this piece is firmly
wedged in and proves difficult to punch out, use a power drill to
bore out as much wood as possible, then punch out the rest. (Edward
R. Lipinski/The New York Times) LITE
